JX Nippon Oil & Energy Corp. said it
will end production of silicon wafers at a unit in December amid
sagging demand for solar products.  The company will continue sales of solar power generation
systems for homes and power stations, Tokyo-based JX Nippon said
today in a  statement .  Silicon wafers are used to convert the sunâ€™s energy into
